      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!--
Encoded for Siddham by Eszter Somogyi, following Ramesh and Tewari's edition unless otherwise noted in comments. Version of January 2019. Comments below by Dániel Balogh are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
-->
        <p><lb n="1"/>valkh<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>ḥ parama-bhaṭṭāraka-pādānuddhyāto mahārāja-bhuluṇḍaḥ samājñāpayati
<lb n="2"/>sarvvān evāsmat-santakān āyuktakān
</p>
        <p>vijñātam astu vaḥ samanujānīmo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>sya valkhā<supplied reason="omitted">yā</supplied><!--
L2. RT: evasmat.
--><!--
L2. Retaining RT's emendation valkhāyām, but once we emend, perhaps sya should also be emended to syāṁ.
--><lb break="no" n="3"/>
m eva bhojikā-bhaṭṭa-bandhulā-pratiṣṭhāpitaka-bappapiśācadevasya pūrvva-bhujyamā<lb break="no" n="4"/>
nakaṁ vibhītakagarttā-grāmasyārddhaṁ devāgrāhāram a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśyam ācandrā<sic>rk</sic>a-
<lb n="5"/>tārakā-kālī<del>n</del>yaṁ devasya bali-caru-satra-dhūpa-gandha-mālyopayojyam idānī<!--
L5. RT: kalī.
--><lb break="no" n="6"/>
m asmābhir anujñātam uc<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>i</corr>
          </choice>tayā devāgrāhāra-bhuktyā pāśupata-deva-prasāda<supplied reason="omitted">kā</supplied><lb break="no" n="7"/>
dyān<choice>
            <sic>ya</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>ṁ devatārttham u<choice>
            <sic>y</sic>
            <corr>p</corr>
          </choice>abhuñjatāṁ kr̥ṣ<choice>
            <sic>ā</sic>
            <corr>a</corr>
          </choice>tā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> ca sarvvair evāsmadīyai<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> samanuma<!--
L7 RT: evasmadīyai
--><lb break="no" n="8"/>
ntavyaṁ</p>
        <p>gomika dūtakaṁ</p>
        <p>varṣe <num value="54"><g type="numeral">50</g> 4</num> vaiśākha śu <num value="3">3</num><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> bhagavac-chiṣ<choice>
            <sic>ṭh</sic>
            <corr>ṭ</corr>
          </choice>ān adhikr̥taḥ<!--
L8. RT: dutakam; vaiśākha su; bhagavac-chiṣṭhan-adhikritaḥ, em. bhagavac-chiṣṭan-adhikritaḥ (sic). I retain what I believe was the intent of RT's emendation. They translate "[This grant is] to be administered by the good [devotees] of Bhagavat (i.e. Lord Nārāyaṇa)." They are probably right, but compare also IN00508:8.
--></p>
        <ab><lb n="01"/>mahārāja-bhuluṇḍasya<!--
